  "body": "Given the access to the database directory of a geth archive node synced to a certain block, we need to be able to produce valid state snapshots for turbo-geth at a certain historical block. The snapshot needs to include the following buckets:\r\n\r\n1. AccountsBucket\r\n2. StorageBucket\r\n3. CodeBucket\r\n4. ContractCodeBucket (in the case where debug.IsThinHistory() is true, which is set by THIN_HISTORY=1 environment variable)\r\n\r\nIt is probably best to create a separate golang project for it, and get both go-ethereum and turbo-geth as dependencies. Luckily, they have different path, so you can use both without confusion.\r\n\r\nThe correctness of the snapshot can be verified by this command:\r\n````\r\nmake state\r\n./build/bin/state --verifySnapshot --block .... --chaindata ....\r\n````",
